  "time_ut": 1656835741,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dbb\u0dcf\u0da2\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba\u0da7 \u0dba\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0db6\u0dd0\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dc0 \u0db4\u0ddc\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0db0\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0dc4\u0dd4\u0dad\u0dca \u0d85\u0db8\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dda",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Police officers are also in trouble as they cannot go to duty",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Police officials in the Western Province say that they are in dire straits as they are unable to go to the police stations to report duties due to lack of fuel.",
        "They point out that a large number of police officers as well as female officers go from their homes daily to the designated police stations by motorbikes and cars and have to face this problem due to lack of fuel for their vehicles.",
        "The officials also say that although filling stations have been set aside to provide fuel for manual services all over the island, most of those filling stations do not provide fuel for police officers' motorcycles and cars.",
        "In this situation, the police officers as well as the officers claim that they are in a difficult situation as they are unable to report their duties during the day as well as at night and are unable to return home after completing their night duties.",
        "They further point out that due to this problematic situation, some police officers as well as officers have to spend the night in police stations and at the homes of friends and relatives of those police officers due to the lack of transport facilities to return home after completing their duties, and the children of their families. The activities have also been severely hampered."
      ],
